Similarly, the radius of the smaller circle is the distance from the origin $O(0, 0)$ to point $Q(7, 0)$, which is $7$.

Since $S(0, k)$ is on the smaller circle, its distance from the origin (which is the radius of the smaller circle) is $7$. Therefore:
